   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject Two Hundred Two THE WHOLE WORLD LIETH IN THE EVIL ONE Scripture: 1 John 5:19 Men are captives of the evil one Once men followed the evil one to commit sin, they became captives of the evil one.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>As soon as a man is born, he is in the position of a captive.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Men are in the power of the Devil To say that man became the Devil s captive means that man fell into the power of the Devil.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>To be in the power of the Devil is to be dominated by him.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Men are lying in the hands of the evil one Men are not only dominated by the Devil, but they are also manipulated by him.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>To be dominated means that one is refused his freedom; even worse, to be manipulated means one is led to act unwittingly, with no consciousness of being manipulated.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>To dominate is to deny one the freedom to do anything; to manipulate is to make one do something without the realization of what he is doing.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>A man lying in the hands of the Devil is like a patient on the operating table who, having been anesthetized, allows the doctor to operate freely.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Give examples to show how man is in the Devil s hand, committing sin without consciousness and without self-control.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>How to escape from the hands of the Devil Confess that you are in the hands of the Devil.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Believe in Jesus as your Savior because He has destroyed the Devil and nullified the works of the Devil.</S>
   </TEXT>
